- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory): The paper is about automata and their properties, which is a topic in formal languages and automata theory.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper involves the study of the minimum length of reset words, which is a logical property of automata.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses the properties of automata and their relation to digraphs, which is a topic in data structures and algorithms.
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory): The paper involves the study of digraphs with large exponent, which is a topic in game theory.
